WEBVTT

00:15.140 --> 00:18.226
<i>For Terry, every day,</i>
<i>means a new murder case,</i>

00:18.852 --> 00:21.771
<i>and a new celebrity guest star</i>
<i>as his partner.</i>

00:22.272 --> 00:26.443
<i>Today's guest:</i>
<i>comedy legend Conan O'Brien.</i>

00:26.943 --> 00:28.611
<i>But here's the catch.</i>

00:28.695 --> 00:30.822
<i>Conan isn't being given a script.</i>

00:30.905 --> 00:33.825
<i>He has no idea what's about to happen.</i>

00:34.325 --> 00:38.872
<i>Together, he and Terry will have</i>
<i>to improvise their way through the case.</i>

00:38.955 --> 00:42.042
<i>But it'll be up to Conan alone</i>
<i>to name the killer.</i>

00:42.834 --> 00:46.087
<i>So join them</i>
<i>as they punch a one-way ticket</i>

00:46.921 --> 00:48.631
<i>to Murderville.</i>

00:52.927 --> 00:54.095
<i>The big city.</i>

00:55.096 --> 00:57.557
<i>Where only the strong survive…</i>

00:57.640 --> 01:00.477
<i>And the ruthless… thrive.</i>

01:01.102 --> 01:02.937
<i>I just made that rhyme up.</i>

01:03.021 --> 01:06.399
<i>No big deal.</i>
<i>I can do all sorts of cool stuff.</i>

01:07.067 --> 01:09.736
<i>My name is Terry Seattle.</i>

01:09.819 --> 01:14.532
<i>I'm a senior homicide detective.</i>
<i>And I am killing it.</i>

01:14.616 --> 01:15.366
Detective.

01:20.371 --> 01:21.372
Morning, Chief.

01:21.456 --> 01:22.499
Pleasure to see you.

01:22.582 --> 01:24.667
Pleasure to see you.
I hope you're doing very well.

01:24.751 --> 01:27.295
I am doing very well. Thank you.

01:27.837 --> 01:30.381
You need to come past the house
and pick up the rest of your crap.

01:30.465 --> 01:33.384
That is not crap, Rhonda,
that's 17 years of marriage.

01:33.468 --> 01:37.096
It's a broken PlayStation 2,
some old <i>Maxim</i> magazines,

01:37.180 --> 01:40.016
a car wash receipt signed by Axl Rose

01:40.099 --> 01:42.310
and a "Take me drunk I'm home" t-shirt.

01:42.393 --> 01:44.771
If you had read
just one of those <i>Maxim</i> articles,

01:44.854 --> 01:46.064
you would know that as a modern male--

01:46.147 --> 01:48.274
Terry, come get your shit
or I'm throwing it out.

01:48.858 --> 01:49.901
Okay?

01:50.693 --> 01:51.653
Okay.

01:53.029 --> 01:56.574
Don't pout, Detective.
I've got a present for you.

01:57.492 --> 01:58.368
A new partner.

01:58.451 --> 02:01.663
No, you can't be serious. Come on,
my life's not going wrong enough as it is

02:01.746 --> 02:03.998
that I gotta babysit
some homicide trainee?

02:04.082 --> 02:06.960
Do you not remember what happened
when I babysat your nephew?

02:07.043 --> 02:09.045
Come on out, Conan.

02:15.635 --> 02:17.011
Come a little closer.

02:19.556 --> 02:21.599
I never liked to presume
how close I can get.

02:21.683 --> 02:23.059
That's just fine.

02:24.060 --> 02:27.730
Terry, meet your new partner,
Conan O'Brien.

02:28.231 --> 02:31.442
Conan, this is senior detective,
Terry Seattle.

02:31.526 --> 02:33.528
Good to see you, sir. How are you?

02:34.237 --> 02:36.197
Got quite a grip on you, huh?

02:38.366 --> 02:40.827
- Yeah.
- Good Lord.

02:48.334 --> 02:51.004
- Yes.
- Yeah, okay. Yeah.

02:51.087 --> 02:52.714
Put your fingers in your ears.

02:54.883 --> 02:56.050
Are you joking?

02:57.427 --> 03:01.097
I mean, did I just turn seven years old?
Because you hired a goddamn clown!

03:01.180 --> 03:03.600
You're the only detective
who can't keep a partner.

03:03.683 --> 03:05.143
Yeah, because they're all idiots!

03:05.226 --> 03:08.146
I mean, look at this guy with his fingers
in his ears. I mean, God!

03:08.229 --> 03:09.022
I can actually,

03:09.105 --> 03:11.900
the fingers don't actually block out
the sound that well,

03:11.983 --> 03:13.985
so I heard clown, I heard idiot.

03:14.068 --> 03:15.653
Terry, make it work.

03:16.404 --> 03:17.655
Nice to meet you.

03:17.739 --> 03:18.823
Let me tell you something.

03:18.907 --> 03:22.911
This ginger monstrosity is the biggest
mistake in the history of city homicide!

03:23.995 --> 03:24.746
No offense.

03:25.330 --> 03:26.414
None taken.

03:26.497 --> 03:27.665
You seem very nervous.

03:27.749 --> 03:31.127
It's my first day on the job
and you're a bit of a legend, so.

03:31.794 --> 03:33.546
It's Terry Seattle. Is that it?

03:33.630 --> 03:37.300
You do more bowing
than a goddamn Tommy Tune.

03:37.383 --> 03:40.678
Okay, bit of an outdated reference
if you ask me, but--

03:41.346 --> 03:42.388
Follow me.

03:52.815 --> 03:54.609
- It's a great office you have here.

03:55.485 --> 03:56.402
Talker.

03:56.486 --> 03:58.196
Yeah. Okay.

03:58.696 --> 04:02.283
Senior detective, Terry Seattle.
And no, I've never been.

04:03.409 --> 04:04.577
That was gonna be my first question.

04:04.661 --> 04:06.037
- Of course it was.
- Yeah.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.538
I got married in Seattle.

04:08.498 --> 04:09.290
What?

04:09.374 --> 04:10.792
I got married in Seattle.

04:10.875 --> 04:12.835
No, I mean, you got married?

04:13.586 --> 04:14.337
Yeah.

04:14.837 --> 04:15.713
To what?

04:16.464 --> 04:17.799
To a wonderful woman.

04:18.675 --> 04:19.842
Does she know?

04:19.926 --> 04:20.760
Uh…

04:21.302 --> 04:23.388
She has an idea.
Let's just put it that way.

04:23.471 --> 04:24.138
Listen,

04:24.222 --> 04:25.932
I hope you don't take this personal,

04:26.015 --> 04:29.602
but I'm not really looking
for a new partner. I already had the best.

04:29.686 --> 04:33.314
Her name was Lori Griffin.
And she was murdered 15 years ago.

04:34.107 --> 04:34.732
Oh…

04:34.816 --> 04:37.318
And out of respect for Lori Griffin,

04:38.069 --> 04:40.697
her desk has remained
completely untouched.

04:41.239 --> 04:42.282
Since that night.

04:42.782 --> 04:45.201
Everything is the same, just the way
she left it. Her case notes,

04:45.785 --> 04:47.287
her uneaten breakfast burrito,

04:47.370 --> 04:50.665
her pet rabbit, Gulliver.
God, I miss that little guy.

04:50.748 --> 04:53.751
You know, you can feed those things
even after the owner's gone.

04:53.835 --> 04:56.129
It would not be respectful to touch it.

04:56.212 --> 04:58.506
Just feed and water them,
a rabbit can live--

04:58.589 --> 04:59.841
Disrespectful.

04:59.924 --> 05:00.717
40 years.

05:00.800 --> 05:01.801
Disrespectful.

05:01.884 --> 05:04.262
What'd you do prior to this,

05:04.345 --> 05:07.473
before you decided to become a homicide
detective? What kind of work were you in?

05:07.557 --> 05:10.643
Been a lot of things.
An entertainer for a while. I, uh--

05:10.727 --> 05:13.021
Yeah. Well, listen,
none of that matters now. Nobody cares.

05:13.104 --> 05:15.523
- Well, you just asked.
- No, but none of it matters.

05:15.606 --> 05:18.318
City homicide
isn't for precious little man-boys

05:18.401 --> 05:21.696
who are afraid to get their lips dirty
and their pants wet. Okay?

05:21.779 --> 05:23.197
No, I wouldn't think so.

05:23.281 --> 05:25.491
'Cause you don't know anything
about getting your lips dirty, do you?

05:25.575 --> 05:27.535
You probably keep your lips real clean.

05:27.618 --> 05:29.787
I can get these lips
as dirty as you want them to be.

05:29.871 --> 05:32.040
Just covered in all kinds of stuff.

05:32.123 --> 05:34.208
City homicide, we're bad dudes.

05:34.876 --> 05:36.544
I'm a bad dude. Are you a bad dude?

05:36.627 --> 05:37.503
Listen,

05:37.587 --> 05:39.380
you are a bad mofo. Everyone knows it.

05:39.464 --> 05:41.883
And I want to get in there. I want
to get my hands dirty, my lips dirty.

05:41.966 --> 05:44.510
I want to solve
whatever case comes our way.

05:45.178 --> 05:46.596
He's got the goods.

05:46.679 --> 05:50.975
He's got what it takes to be a hard-ass,
homicide detective trainee.

05:51.059 --> 05:53.978
Well, that's good news.
Because there's been a murder.

05:54.062 --> 05:55.146
What?

05:55.688 --> 05:59.400
A magician performing
at the grand opening of the city library

05:59.484 --> 06:01.778
sawed his assistant in half

06:01.861 --> 06:03.696
but couldn't put her back together again.

06:03.780 --> 06:06.365
Classic Humpty Dumpty.

06:06.449 --> 06:08.993
I need you two down there on the double.

06:10.620 --> 06:11.788
Goodbye, Chief.

06:12.371 --> 06:13.790
You ready to go solve this murder?

06:13.873 --> 06:15.458
I am. I'm ready to go.

06:15.541 --> 06:17.460
- Yeah, let's get going.
- All right.

06:18.336 --> 06:19.962
<i>We took my '82 Dodge Rampage</i>

06:20.046 --> 06:22.632
<i>over to the library to check out</i>
<i>the crime scene.</i>

06:23.257 --> 06:26.677
<i>It was time for Conan</i>
<i>to take off his training diaper</i>

06:26.761 --> 06:29.347
<i>and start pooping his pants</i>
<i>like a big boy.</i>

06:29.430 --> 06:31.933
Terry Seattle, Senior Detec--
Doesn't matter.

06:32.517 --> 06:35.728
You don't need to show--
we're in a crime scene, okay?

06:36.312 --> 06:39.107
I think we should find out
what the hell went on here.

06:39.190 --> 06:40.775
- Officers.
- Officers.

06:41.275 --> 06:42.777
I already said officers.

06:42.860 --> 06:43.653
Okay.

06:46.197 --> 06:48.116
Well, well, look at this guy.

06:48.199 --> 06:49.659
<i>Hola</i>, Seattle.

06:50.326 --> 06:51.577
You must be Terry's new partner.

06:51.661 --> 06:54.122
Yes. I'm his new partner, Conan O'Brien.
What's your name?

06:54.205 --> 06:56.833
Detective Darren Phillips.
Most people call me Daz.

06:56.916 --> 06:58.417
Nobody call-- I don't call you Daz at all.

06:58.501 --> 06:59.127
It's a pleasure.

06:59.210 --> 07:01.671
Detective Phillips, honor to see you.
What's going on?

07:01.754 --> 07:05.007
All right, stop schmoozing with this guy.
What's wrong? You're just embarrassing.

07:05.091 --> 07:07.426
Just tell him it's our crime scene
and get the hell out of here.

07:07.510 --> 07:10.304
Hey, this is our crime scene.
We're taking lead on this one.

07:10.388 --> 07:14.267
We understand
there's been a homicide murder.

07:14.892 --> 07:20.231
Uh, victim sawed in half during some kind
of magical performance, if you will.

07:20.314 --> 07:22.525
Why are you telling him? He's an officer.

07:22.608 --> 07:25.987
I'm reviewing the facts
of what I've heard so far.

07:26.070 --> 07:29.157
Let's continue.
Sir, please. How can we help?

07:29.240 --> 07:30.450
What do we got here?

07:30.533 --> 07:32.368
This gentleman is Captivating Keith.

07:32.452 --> 07:35.163
It was his assistant
who got sawed in half.

07:35.246 --> 07:37.957
I don't know what happened, man.

07:38.833 --> 07:40.877
My assistant, Sarah and me, we just--

07:40.960 --> 07:43.713
we did the same routine we've always done.

07:43.796 --> 07:45.673
Somebody must have gone in
and they must have

07:45.756 --> 07:48.759
replaced the trick saw with a real saw.

07:48.843 --> 07:53.055
The blood. There, there, blood.
It's just everywhere! Blood!

07:53.139 --> 07:56.642
Did you think at any point
when there was all that blood

07:56.726 --> 07:59.770
that maybe you should stop sawing?
Did that occur to you?

08:00.730 --> 08:01.397
Maybe.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.691
Did you have a safe word
that you normally employ?

08:03.774 --> 08:05.943
- Of course we had a safe word.
- Okay.

08:06.444 --> 08:09.322
If anything was to go wrong, my assistant
was supposed to shout, "Stop!"

08:09.405 --> 08:11.991
But all I heard was,
"Keith, you're sawing me in half."

08:13.242 --> 08:16.204
- I guess it's not the safe word.
- No, they're not the same.

08:16.287 --> 08:18.372
- Yeah, well… Really isn't.
- There's rules.

08:19.123 --> 08:20.750
We're sorry for your loss.

08:21.250 --> 08:22.001
Thank you.

08:22.919 --> 08:23.836
Amber.

08:23.920 --> 08:27.715
This is Amber Kang. Forensics.

08:28.633 --> 08:29.509
Nice to see you.

08:29.592 --> 08:31.594
- Wow, wow, wow.
- Uh…

08:31.677 --> 08:36.390
Homicide detective, Kang Coroner… Uh…

08:36.474 --> 08:37.850
- What…?
- What? I'm sorry.

08:37.934 --> 08:40.895
What are you doing?
You're embarrassing, you're so nerv--

08:40.978 --> 08:42.188
I got nervous.

08:42.271 --> 08:43.814
Amber, um…

08:43.898 --> 08:49.820
we'd like to know what's happening here.
State of the body… dead, I presume.

08:49.904 --> 08:50.738
Very dead.

08:50.821 --> 08:52.782
What've we got here, Amber?

08:52.865 --> 08:54.909
Let me take you over to the murder weapon.

08:54.992 --> 08:57.995
Now, here's something interesting.
No fingerprints.

08:58.496 --> 09:01.290
But, you'll never guess
what I did find on the handle.

09:01.374 --> 09:03.000
Traces of hot sauce.

09:03.084 --> 09:04.126
Wow!

09:04.210 --> 09:06.504
- Hot sauce on the handle.
- Spicy.

09:07.088 --> 09:09.423
The body is right there.

09:09.507 --> 09:11.217
And you're being a total clown.

09:11.717 --> 09:12.927
Now, just take it easy.

09:13.010 --> 09:17.431
Uh… traces of hot sauce. Were you able
to trace what kind of hot sauce?

09:17.515 --> 09:21.644
Not yet, but we also found
trace amounts of pet hair.

09:21.727 --> 09:23.813
Most likely a small animal.

09:24.397 --> 09:24.981
Interesting.

09:25.064 --> 09:26.941
What are you thinking?
Maybe a beagle out for revenge?

09:29.277 --> 09:30.528
Anything else, Amber?

09:30.611 --> 09:32.947
Well, did you take a look at the suitcase?

09:33.656 --> 09:36.576
Says this is where
Captivating Keith kept his trick saw.

09:36.659 --> 09:38.911
Now apparently,
he was the only one with a key

09:38.995 --> 09:42.456
so someone must have picked the lock,
switched the saws.

09:42.540 --> 09:44.292
Excuse me, Mr. Policeman.

09:44.959 --> 09:45.918
Yes?

09:46.544 --> 09:49.213
When is the magician
going to finish the trick?

09:49.297 --> 09:50.506
Uh…

09:51.257 --> 09:51.966
Well,

09:52.049 --> 09:54.135
I'm gonna look at some evidence

09:54.218 --> 09:56.429
and this tall, young gentleman here

09:56.512 --> 09:59.181
will be happy to answer
any of your questions.

09:59.265 --> 10:00.266
So…

10:01.225 --> 10:02.393
Hello, what's your name?

10:02.476 --> 10:05.479
When is the magician
going to put the lady back together?

10:06.063 --> 10:06.689
Well,

10:07.481 --> 10:09.942
the lady can't go back together

10:10.610 --> 10:12.153
because what happened,

10:12.236 --> 10:13.654
is the magician

10:13.738 --> 10:15.906
really sawed her in half,

10:15.990 --> 10:17.241
cut through skin,

10:17.325 --> 10:19.744
ligament, muscle, bone.

10:19.827 --> 10:23.372
She had instantaneous,
probably 90% blood loss

10:23.456 --> 10:25.666
and then she went into that black void

10:26.876 --> 10:28.002
known as death.

10:28.753 --> 10:30.171
Where there is no return.

10:30.671 --> 10:33.382
She's gone. Gone forever.

10:33.466 --> 10:35.968
What does that all even mean? I don't--

10:36.052 --> 10:36.969
She's dead.

10:37.053 --> 10:38.804
- I just don't understand--
- She's so dead.

10:38.888 --> 10:40.765
I just don't understand.
Is magic real or not?

10:40.848 --> 10:42.558
It's a very simple question, sir.
It's a yes or no!

10:42.642 --> 10:43.517
It's not magic.

10:43.601 --> 10:44.518
It is magic.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.103
- God.
- Look at the sign behind you.

10:46.604 --> 10:50.733
Yeah, I know.
That's what grown-ups call a lie.

10:50.816 --> 10:51.776
Is this what dying is?

10:51.859 --> 10:54.945
That's what I told you.
Yes, this is what dying is like.

10:55.029 --> 10:56.364
She'll go to heaven, right?

10:56.989 --> 10:58.407
Oh, well, I don't know.

10:58.491 --> 11:00.910
Will she still be in two pieces
when she's in heaven?

11:00.993 --> 11:04.705
Well, no, my guess is,
before they put her in the ground--

11:04.789 --> 11:07.041
All right, trainee, let's go.
We found some new evidence.

11:07.124 --> 11:09.251
Was on my knee for a long time.

11:09.752 --> 11:13.881
<i>Our first suspect was</i>
<i>Captivating Keith's former assistant, Deb.</i>

11:14.382 --> 11:16.258
<i>She'd recently been fired and replaced</i>

11:16.342 --> 11:19.720
<i>with the much younger</i>
<i>and now much deader, Sarah.</i>

11:21.764 --> 11:24.183
Welcome to Quirky Jack's Homestyle Eatery.

11:24.266 --> 11:27.770
Where we serve heaping portions of whimsy
and medium-sized portions of food.

11:27.853 --> 11:29.438
My name is Deb, I'll be your server.

11:29.522 --> 11:33.901
Can I start you off with a bowl
of our world-famous deep-fried chowder?

11:33.984 --> 11:36.195
We're not really hungry for food, Deb.

11:37.029 --> 11:39.365
We are hungry for answers.

11:39.990 --> 11:42.118
Is this about what happened to Sarah
at Keith's magic show?

11:42.201 --> 11:44.245
That's right.
It is about what happened to Sarah.

11:44.328 --> 11:46.997
Okay. Listen, I'll talk to you,
but you're gonna have to order something

11:47.081 --> 11:48.582
because otherwise
my boss is gonna get mad.

11:48.666 --> 11:49.750
Okay. Yeah, well, I could eat something.

11:49.834 --> 11:51.836
Sure, yeah. I'll have…

11:51.919 --> 11:53.879
Oh, you know what,
they got the sloppy jalapeñ-joes.

11:54.380 --> 11:57.174
They're back. Yeah, we'll take
two of those. The sloppy jalapeñ-joes.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.760
Do you want to add two sloparitas
for five bucks more?

11:59.844 --> 12:03.305
- Let's do it.
- Two, <i>dos,</i> sloparitas.

12:03.389 --> 12:04.932
- Yes.
- I'll be back with your food.

12:05.015 --> 12:07.226
You're gonna love
this sloppy jalapeñ-joes.

12:07.309 --> 12:09.728
You have never had a wetter sandwich.
It's unbelievable.

12:09.812 --> 12:11.272
All right.
Well, I'm looking forward to it.

12:11.355 --> 12:14.817
It's like eating throw up.
That's delicious.

12:16.026 --> 12:19.321
All right, we got two sloppy jalapeñ-joes.

12:19.405 --> 12:20.990
Yes, we sure do.

12:23.159 --> 12:26.203
And two sloparitas.

12:26.287 --> 12:28.247
Two sloparitas.

12:28.330 --> 12:33.294
This is good. And you gotta try
some of this signature spicy slop sauce.

12:33.794 --> 12:35.337
You know,
it just makes it extra sloppy.

12:35.421 --> 12:37.173
That is extremely hot…

12:37.256 --> 12:40.384
Yeah. That's good.
You have never had a sloppier sandwich.

12:40.468 --> 12:42.178
- Okay.

12:42.845 --> 12:44.388
- Get right into it, huh?
- Yup. Eat up.

12:44.472 --> 12:45.890
Yeah, I got other tables, so…

12:45.973 --> 12:48.559
Well, I don't have other murders. So.

12:48.642 --> 12:50.186
- God, it's wet.
- Okay.

12:50.269 --> 12:51.479
Yeah, okay.

12:51.562 --> 12:53.147
That is a sloppy sandwich.

12:56.650 --> 12:59.069
- I tried to warn you.
- Yeah.

13:01.322 --> 13:03.491
All right, you got some questions
in your notebook.

13:03.574 --> 13:05.493
Yeah, did you have questions for me?

13:06.285 --> 13:08.078
Go ahead. Shoot.
This is your time to shine.

13:08.162 --> 13:10.956
- Jesus Christ.
- Hey, we haven't got all day.

13:11.040 --> 13:12.666
Okay, I'm sorry.

13:12.750 --> 13:14.543
Wanna take another bite first?
Are you hungry?

13:15.878 --> 13:19.798
Let me get that sloppy for you.
You've never had a sloppy sandwich.

13:19.882 --> 13:22.051
- Well, this is great.
- Just slop it. Really slop it.

13:22.134 --> 13:24.094
No, it's great.
It's very aggressive on your part.

13:24.595 --> 13:25.596
Oh, my God.

13:29.683 --> 13:30.726
Go ahead.

13:34.772 --> 13:36.190
Dive in there, Conan.

13:37.024 --> 13:39.235
Is it true Captivating Keith

13:39.860 --> 13:43.405
replaced you with Sarah
'cause he thought you'd gotten too old?

13:48.285 --> 13:50.913
Jesus Christ, Conan.
What the hell's wrong with you?

